  "texts": [
    "ColBERT contains three components, a query encoder (𝑓 𝑄), a document encoder (𝑓 𝐷), and an interaction machine, all of which are shown in Figure 8.",
    "ColBERT provides a novel approach to identifying the interactions between a query and a document.",
    "The query and the document are first encoded separately via BERT to store the word embeddings, and the similarity between each query embedding and all document embeddings is then calculated via an interaction machine to obtain the maximum score.",
    "Finally, all the maximum scores of the query-document token pairs are integrated to determine the relevance between the query and the document.",
    "The authors conducted experiments on the MS MARCO and the TREC CAR datasets, and provided a comparison with BERT Base on the reranking and the end-to-end tasks in terms of MRR@10."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}